<h1>Information Base Files</h1>
IB files are where all of your information that you add to Ideaspad is kept.<BR>
IB files have IBF and IBW file extensions, if you wish to backup your information you could just copy these two files.<BR><BR>

You can have up to nineteen different IB files (or four if you have the shareware version).<BR>
You can use files for different purposes or themes.

<br><br>
<H1>Maintenance Screen</h1>
To create, delete, rename and open files use the maintenance screen.
<br>
This can be found on the 'Information Base' selection screen (not available on your first use of the program)
<br><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="gfx/maintenance.png" width="328" height="287">
<br><br>
The fifth option is 'Repair and Compact' is a feature which helps to keep the IB file fit and healthy.<BR>
IB files can grow quite large, using this option can help to reduce the size.

